{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κροτ-έω</b>, <br /> <i>poetry</i> <b>κορτέω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus, compare ἀνακροτέω: (κρότος)\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]:— <b>make to rattle</b>, of horses, ὄχεα κροτέοντες <b>rattling</b> them <b>along</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.453, compare “Hymnus ad Apollinem” 234. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>knock, strike</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" λέβητας 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.58; θύρσῳ γῆν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 188; τοῖς ἀγκῶσι τὰς πλευράς 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 54.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.10d: obscene meaning, “IG” 12(7).414 (Amorgos, compare διακροτέω 1):\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <b>to be beaten</b> byrain, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “NA” 16.17. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>clap</b> in sign of applause, κ. τὰς χεῖρας, τὼ χεῖρε, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.60, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cyr.” 8.4.12; ταῖς χερσί Theophrastus Philosophus [{4-3rd c.BC}] “Characteres” 19.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>applaud</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Smp.” 9.4, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.226, etc.; ἐν θεάτρῳ Theophrastus Philosophus [{4-3rd c.BC}] “Characteres” 11.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: c.<i>accusative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κ. τινά 3rd c.AD: Diogenes Laertius 7.173 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Po.” 1456a10 (sed to be read κρατεῖσθαι), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ax.” 368d, etc.; τέλειος ῥήτωρ καὶ κεκροτημένος 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 2.128 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus; παρὰ Ὁμήρῳ κεκρότηται τὰ σώφρονα συμπόσια\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>are commended</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 5.182a (sed to be read &lt;συγ&gt;κεκρ.). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> also in sign of disapproval, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.533a. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> κ. ὀδόντας <b>gnash</b> the teeth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus “Supp.” 2.9. \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> of a smith, <b>hammer, weld together</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Lex.” 9: _metaphorically_, in \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<i>passive</i>, <b>to be wrought</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κεκρότηται χρυσέα κρηπίς 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “fragment” 194, compare 3rd c.BC: Lycophron Tragicus 888: hence ἐξ ἀπάτας κεκροτημένοι ἄνδρες\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>one mass</b> of trickery, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.49; εὐθὺς τὸ πρῆγμα κροτείσθω 'strike while the iron is hot', “AP” 10.20 (from Adaeus). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>rattle, clash</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" χαλκώματα Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus [{1-2nd c.AD}] 2.944b \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: with <i>dative</i>, κ. ὀστράκοις καὶ ψήφοις <b>make a rattling noise</b> with them, in order to collect a swarm of bees, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “HA” 627a16; κ. κυμβάλοις 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Alex.” 9 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; satirically, ἡ τοῖς ὀστράκοις κροτοῦσα [Μοῦσ᾽ Εὐριπίδου] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ra.” 1306, compare 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “NA” 2.11. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <b>strike the woof home with the weaver's sley</b>, σινδόνες λίαν κεκροτημέναι <b>close-woven</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 15.1.67. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8104","accentedUnicode":"κροτέω","shortDef":"to clap","mediumDef":"to clap","stepGloss":"to clap","stepTransliteration":"kroteō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}